Example for Running Simulation using Nanosim

Command (Option 1): nanosim -n Example.sp -c Example_Option_1.cfg -nvec Example.vec -out fsdb -z tt

Command (Option 2): nanosim -n Example.sp -c Example_Option_2.cfg -nvec Example.vec -out out -z tt

Arguments:

* The following options can be used based on the requirements.

1) "-n" --> It is used to specify the netlist.

2) "-cfg" --> It is used to specify the configuration file.

3) "-nvec" --> It is used to specify the vector file.

4) "-out" --> It is used to specify the format of the output file.

Notice 1: The "fsdb" format is used for generation of the waveform information.

Notice 2: The "out" format is used for generation of the output files.

5) "-z" --> It is used to instruct the tool to create the technology files with having "tt" at the beginning of their name.
